00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:37,791
AND THE WYNNIT VARIETY
IS BY FAR MY FAVORITE.

216
00:10:37,875 --> 00:10:40,041
- YOU THINK SO?

217
00:10:40,125 --> 00:10:41,750
- IS THIS A NEW RECIPE, THOUGH?

218
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:43,166
IT'S KIND OF DIFFERENT,
BUT IT'S GOOD.

219
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:45,500
- HMM.

220
00:10:45,583 --> 00:10:47,125
- WHAT'S WRONG?
- NOTHING.

221
00:10:47,208 --> 00:10:50,166
- THE RECIPE'S SCORED HIGH MARKS
WITH YOUR PARTNER, MISS FERRIS.

222
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:52,333
I TOLD YOU IT WOULD, DIDN'T I?

223
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:54,416
- UH, THAT'S ENOUGH.

224
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:55,791
- WHAT YOU'RE EATING, YOUNG MAN,

225
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:59,125
IS A BRAND NEW CONCOCTION MISS
FERRIS CAME UP WITH.

226
00:10:59,208 --> 00:11:03,125
- YOU INVENTED THIS FLAVOR
ALL BY YOURSELF?

227
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:05,000
- I'VE GOT SOME
SERIOUS COMPETITION

228
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:07,458
WHEN SHE FINALLY OPENS UP HER
OWN DANGO SHOP.

229
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:10,375
- WAIT, WHEN SHE WHAT?
OF COURSE.

230
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:11,875
WHY DIDN'T I SEE IT BEFORE?

231
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:13,833
NO ONE'S TAKES DANGO MORE
SERIOUSLY THAN YOU.

232
00:11:13,916 --> 00:11:15,833
- BECAUSE UNLIKE
SOME PEOPLE I KNOW,

233
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:17,916
I'M FULLY AWARE OF HOW IMPORTANT
IT IS TO PAY MY RESPECTS

234
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,166
TO THE GREAT DANGO GOD!

235
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:21,125
- YEAH, ABOUT THAT...
DANGO GOD?

236
00:11:21,208 --> 00:11:23,291
- HE IS THE ARBITER
OF ALL THINGS EXQUISITE.

237
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,958
THOSE WHO IGNORE HIM TURN THEIR
BACKS ON THE WHOLE WORLD.

238
00:11:26,041 --> 00:11:28,958
- AND THEY DO SO AT THEIR PERIL!
- OKAY.

239
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:32,583
- Claugh: HEY, HEY!
IF IT ISN'T HE WHO NAPS.

240
00:11:32,666 --> 00:11:34,541
- YEAH. PLEASE FORGIVE
OUR LITTLE INTRUSION.

241
00:11:34,625 --> 00:11:36,708
WE'VE COME HERE
TO COMMANDEER YOUR SERVICES.

242
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:38,666
- Claugh: ON YOUR FEET!
- ( loud thumping )

243
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:39,916
- Ryner: WHAT THE HELL?

244
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,625
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING! GET
YOUR HANDS OFF ME!

245
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,958
- WE CAN DO THIS THE HARD WAY
OR THE EASY WAY.

246
00:11:44,041 --> 00:11:45,875
I CAN'T GET ON MY FEET
IF YOU'RE DRAGGING ME!

247
00:11:45,958 --> 00:11:47,875
- SO THE SORRY LETCH'S
CALAMITOUS MISDEEDS

248
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:49,083
FINALLY CATCH UP WITH HIM.

249
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,708
- ( chattering indistinctly )

250
00:11:54,541 --> 00:11:56,750
- NICE TO HAVE KNOWN YOU,
PERVERT.

251
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:07,625
- Sion: CAN'T WE GO FASTER?

252
00:12:07,708 --> 00:12:09,375
- NO, SIR!
IT'S ALREADY TOO DANGEROUS!

253
00:12:09,458 --> 00:12:12,583
- DAMN IT. THE PREPARATIONS
SHOULD BE IN PLACE BY NOW.

254
00:12:19,916 --> 00:12:24,708
- ( chuckling ) THE JIG IS UP.
NO ESCAPE FOR YOU.

255
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:31,416
AT LAST, THE MOMENT
I'VE BEEN DREAMING OF.

256
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:33,083
THE REDHEADED WALL OF
MEAT THAT'S HAD ME

257
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:34,375
IN VIRTUAL SHACKLES FOR DAYS

258
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:36,125
IS JUST AS BAD AS YOU ARE!
AND YOU...

259
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:38,250
WHAT THE HELL GIVES
YOU THE RIGHT TO RUN

260
00:12:38,333 --> 00:12:39,458
YOUR HAPPY ASS OUT OF TOWN

261
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:40,500
- WHILE I'M TREATED
LIKE A FREAKING SLAVE!

262
00:12:40,583 --> 00:12:41,958
- KNOCK IT OFF!

263
00:12:42,041 --> 00:12:44,750
WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?
ARE YOU MICE OR ARE YOU MEN?

264
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,083
- ( all chuckling )

265
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:52,083
- ( all yelling )

266
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:53,500
- Sion: WHAT IS THE
MEANING OF THIS?

267
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:56,625
- THAT'S RIGHT, MEN! AWAY!

268
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:58,416
- COME ON! COME ON!
LET'S GO! THIS WAY!

269
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,625
- I HAVE WORK TO DO!
PUT ME DOWN THIS INSTANT...

270
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:03,458
- BYE! HAVE FUN.

271
00:13:03,541 --> 00:13:06,875
- ♪ FOR HE'S A JOLLY-GOOD FELLOW
FOR HE'S A JOLLY-GOOD FELLOW ♪

272
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:20,541
- ( people cheering )

273
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:24,000
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO YOU,
YOUR MAJESTY!

274
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:25,750
- I CAN SEE HIM!

275
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:27,708
- HAPPY BIRTHDAY, SION!
- YOUR MAJESTY!

276
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,958
- SIR. WE'RE ALL WAITING
ON YOU, YOUR MAJESTY.

277
00:13:34,041 --> 00:13:37,208
I KNOW IT'S SHORT NOTICE, BUT
COULD YOU IGNITE THE FIREWORKS?

278
00:13:37,291 --> 00:13:38,333
- I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

279
00:13:38,416 --> 00:13:40,416
- WE PREPARED THEM
ESPECIALLY FOR YOU.

280
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,291
- BUT THAT'S ABSURDLY
EXTRAVAGANT. THE BUDGET WON'T...

281
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:46,750
- COME ON! JUST HAVE A LOOK.

282
00:13:46,833 --> 00:13:48,958
- MAY ALL YOUR WISHES
COME TRUE, MY KING!

283
00:13:49,041 --> 00:13:51,625
- I LOVE YOU, YOUR MAJESTY!

284
00:13:51,708 --> 00:13:54,291
- SEEMS EVERYONE IN THE KINGDOM
IS READY TO CELEBRATE THIS DAY

285
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:55,666
BUT YOU, SIR.

286
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,541
- SURELY IT WOULD BE GOOD FORM
TO REPAY THE HONOR.

287
00:13:57,625 --> 00:14:00,375
- I SUPPOSE YOU'RE
RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

288
00:14:00,458 --> 00:14:03,000
- TRAIN YOUR EYES ON THE
MOUNTAIN RANGE IN FRONT OF US.

289
00:14:03,083 --> 00:14:05,625
FIRE AN IZUCHI IN THE DIRECTION
OF THAT TINY FLECK OF LIGHT

290
00:14:05,708 --> 00:14:07,166
WHEN YOU'RE READY.

291
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,791
- THAT I CAN DO.

292
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,625
WHAT I SEEK IS THUNDER.
IZUCHI!

293
00:14:26,041 --> 00:14:27,750
- ( singing in Japanese )

294
00:14:56,958 --> 00:14:58,583
- THAT'S SO COOL!
- WOW!

295
00:15:04,541 --> 00:15:08,333
- All: AND HAPPY BIRTHDAY
TO OUR VERY FAVORITE CAPTAIN!

296
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:10,083
- SERIOUSLY, YOU GUYS?

297
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:14,333
- FEAST YOUR EYES
ON THIS LITTLE WISH.

298
00:15:14,416 --> 00:15:17,166
- Milk: "HAPPY BIRTHDAY"

299
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:20,125
- I'M SPEECHLESS. YOU...
- AHEM...

300
00:15:20,208 --> 00:15:21,791
- All: YOUR ATTENTION
PLEASE, CAPTAIN.

301
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:24,916
- NOW, ARE WE READY, GENTLEMEN?
FIVE!

302
00:15:25,583 --> 00:15:27,208
- FOUR!
- THREE!

303
00:15:27,291 --> 00:15:29,875
- TWO!
- AND ONE!

304
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:38,875
- ( giggling )

305
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,583
- ( people chattering )

306
00:16:08,458 --> 00:16:10,708
- HEY, JUST WHERE
DOES HE THINK HE'S GOING?

307
00:16:10,791 --> 00:16:13,125
- RIGHT. NO MORE WINE,
I PROMISE.

308
00:16:18,166 --> 00:16:19,583
- YOU'RE LEAVING?

309
00:16:31,166 --> 00:16:33,833
- OH! HELLO, YOUR MAJESTY.
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

310
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:37,166
- PREPARE THE CARRIAGE, PLEASE.
I THINK I'D LIKE TO TAKE IT OUT.

311
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:39,208
- YES, SIR. I'LL CALL
FOR A COACHMAN AT ONCE.

312
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:41,083
- OH, I'LL DRIVE MYSELF.

313
00:16:41,166 --> 00:16:45,083
- SIR?
- I'VE SOMEONE TO PICK UP.

314
00:16:45,166 --> 00:16:50,583
WELL, THAT IS... SOMEONE TO
WHOM I OWE A GREAT DEBT.

315
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,750
- ( thunder rumbling )

316
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:16,000
- AND OF COURSE,
IT STARTS POURING.

317
00:17:16,083 --> 00:17:18,666
OKAY, THEN,
TIME TO HEAD BACK, I THINK.

318
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:41,791
THANKS.
YOU'RE A REAL LIFE-SAVER.

319
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:43,750
- IT IS I WHO SHOULD
BE THANKING YOU.

320
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:45,750
- HUH? FOR WHAT?

321
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:48,375
- YOU ARE THE ONE RESPONSIBLE
FOR THE FIREWORKS THIS EVENING,

322
00:17:48,458 --> 00:17:49,500
ARE YOU NOT?

323
00:17:49,583 --> 00:17:52,708
- OH, THAT. WELL, YEAH.

324
00:17:52,791 --> 00:17:54,166
- THE ROAD'S A BIT TREACHEROUS.

325
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:56,375
DO YOU MIND IF WE STOP OFF
SOMEWHERE FOR A WHILE?

326
00:17:56,458 --> 00:17:57,500
- JUST TO BE SAFE?

327
00:17:57,583 --> 00:17:59,541
- YOU'RE DRIVING. DO
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

328
00:17:59,625 --> 00:18:01,083
- VERY WELL, THEN.

329
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:09,083
- HUH. CONVENIENT, HUH?

330
00:18:09,166 --> 00:18:11,583
THIS PLACE BRINGS BACK
A LOT OF MEMORIES, DOESN'T IT?

331
00:18:11,666 --> 00:18:15,625
- I SHOULD HOPE SO. IT'S WHERE
I FIRST MADE MY OFFER TO YOU...

332
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:17,916
- RYNER?
- HUH?

333
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,333
- WHEN I SAID THANK YOU
FOR TONIGHT, I DID MEAN IT.

334
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:24,208
- YEAH, WELL, I GUESS EVEN I
CAN BE NICE SOMETIMES.

335
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:25,375
BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,

336
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,083
I'M TOTALLY TAKING A NAP
WHEN WE GET BACK.

337
00:18:28,166 --> 00:18:30,583
- DON'T START COUNTING SHEEP
JUST YET, MY FRIEND.

338
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:31,916
THERE'S STILL WORK TO BE DONE.

339
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,916
- OH, COME ON, GIVE IT A REST.

340
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,875
YOU REALLY ARE GOING TO HAVE
MY DEATH ON YOUR CONSCIENCE

341
00:18:35,958 --> 00:18:37,458
IF THIS KEEPS UP.

342
00:18:37,541 --> 00:18:39,583
- I SUPPOSE WORKING FOR
TEN DAYS WITHOUT A BREAK

343
00:18:39,666 --> 00:18:41,083
DOESN'T COME EASILY TO YOU.

344
00:18:41,166 --> 00:18:42,416
- YEAH, ABOUT THAT,

345
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,000
IT'D HAVE BEEN NICE IF
YOU'D RECOGNIZED THAT

346
00:18:44,083 --> 00:18:47,041
A COUPLE OF DAYS INTO IT
OR ON THE FIRST DAY.

347
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:48,541
- MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

348
00:18:48,625 --> 00:18:50,791
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE HEAD BACK,
GET OURSELVES SOME SLEEP?

349
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:53,875
- HELL, YES!
BEST PLAN YOU'VE EVER HAD.

350
00:18:53,958 --> 00:18:56,500
- YOU'LL BE AT THE INN?
I'LL SEND A CARRIAGE FOR YOU

351
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:58,500
SO WE CAN PICK UP
WHERE WE LEFT OFF.

352
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:02,041
- NICE TRY.
- WILL THREE HOURS DO THE TRICK?

353
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:04,083
- WHAT? I'M SLEEP DEPRIVED HERE!

354
00:19:04,166 --> 00:19:06,250
I'M GOING TO NEED A LOT MORE
THAN THREE FREAKING HOURS!

355
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,916
- HOW MANY HOURS
WOULD YOU LIKE ME TO WAIT?

356
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,458
- HOW ABOUT THREE HUNDRED?

357
00:19:10,541 --> 00:19:13,666
- FUNNY, BUT AFRAID NOT. HOW
ABOUT I SEND FOR YOU IN FOUR?

358
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:15,208
- THAT'S NOT EVEN FAIR!

359
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,500
I'M NOT THE ONLY PERSON YOU
SHOULD BE THINKING ABOUT HERE.

360
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:21,166
YOU PROBABLY HAVEN'T HAD PROPER
SLEEP IN GOD KNOWS HOW LONG.

361
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:23,625
- IT'S THE NATURE OF THE
BEAST AND THE PRICE I PAY

362
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:25,375
FOR WANTING TO CHANGE THE WORLD.

363
00:19:25,458 --> 00:19:26,916
WE STILL NEED BETTER EDUCATION,

364
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,125
AND HEALTH REFORM,
AND LOWER TAXES.

365
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:31,333
OUR TECHNOLOGICAL
INFRASTRUCTURE IS FRAUGHT.

366
00:19:31,416 --> 00:19:33,083
THAT'S JUST THE START, SO...

367
00:19:33,166 --> 00:19:35,041
- SERIOUSLY, HOW LONG ARE YOU
GOING TO RUN YOURSELF

368
00:19:35,125 --> 00:19:37,500
INTO THE GROUND OVER THIS CRAP?

369
00:19:37,583 --> 00:19:39,250
UH, LISTEN, SION...

370
00:19:54,875 --> 00:19:58,833
I DON'T MEAN TO
COMPLAIN SO MUCH.

371
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:01,291
BACK IN THE DAY
WHEN YOU FIRST MADE THAT OFFER

372
00:20:01,375 --> 00:20:03,250
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
OUT OF YOUR MIND.

373
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:07,166
I STILL DO, BUT I DON'T KNOW.

374
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:09,333
THE FACT THAT YOU WANTED
TO CHANGE THINGS,

375
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:11,916
IT MEANT A LOT TO ME EVEN THEN.

376
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,791
FEW PEOPLE CARE ENOUGH
TO BE WILLING TO HELP

377
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,750
THEIR FELLOW MEN
RISE ABOVE IT ALL.

378
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:22,375
YOUR DREAM WASN'T AN EMPTY ONE.

379
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:28,416
THIS COUNTRY'S CHANGED.
YOU'VE CHANGED IT.

380
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:32,333
WE LIVE IN A WORLD NOW WHERE
PEOPLE CAN JUST CLOSE THEIR EYES

381
00:20:32,416 --> 00:20:35,416
ON A LATE AFTERNOON AND NAP.

382
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:38,958
- BUT IT IS AN EMPTY DREAM.

383
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:44,291
HOW MANY GOOD PEOPLE
HAVE DIED TO MAKE IT HAPPEN?

384
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:46,125
HOW MANY MORE WILL HAVE TO?

385
00:20:46,208 --> 00:20:49,291
HOW MANY WILL SURVIVE
LONG ENOUGH TO SEE IT?

386
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:51,125
HOW MANY FRIENDS
MUST I SACRIFICE

387
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,291
TO THE WORST OF THIS WORLD
BEFORE IT CHANGES?

388
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:55,291
- NOW YOU'RE BROODING.
SURE IT'S A HARD ROAD,

389
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:56,833
BUT THIS COUNTRY WOULDN'T
HAVE TAKEN THE FIRST STEP

390
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,833
WITHOUT YOU.

391
00:20:58,916 --> 00:21:02,458
PLEASE, LOOK AT WHAT
YOU'VE ACCOMPLISHED.

392
00:21:05,708 --> 00:21:08,000
I KNOW YOU WORK HARD
BECAUSE YOU FEEL GUILTY,

393
00:21:08,083 --> 00:21:10,166
AND IT KILLS ME TO SEE IT.

394
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:13,041
BUT YOU CAN'T CHANGE THINGS
BY PUNISHING YOURSELF.

395
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:19,041
AND WHATEVER YOU THINK,
THINGS HAVE CHANGED.

396
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:21,250
YOU CAN AFFORD TO TAKE IT
EASY ONCE IN A WHILE.

397
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:23,375
THE WORLD WILL WAIT.

398
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:25,083
THERE'S NO POINT IN
SECOND-GUESSING YOURSELF

399
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,833
IF ALL IT DOES IS
PARALYZE YOU, RIGHT?

400
00:21:27,916 --> 00:21:29,666
TAKE MY WORD FOR IT.

401
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,958
AND BESIDES,
YOU'VE GOT HELP, YOU KNOW.

402
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,583
THAT INTENSE REDHEADED BRUTE,

403
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:36,291
THE GUYS IN THE TABOO
BREAKER SQUADRON,

404
00:21:36,375 --> 00:21:38,250
HELL, EVEN FERRIS AND I
ARE ON BOARD...

405
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:39,541
AND LIKE IT OR NOT,
YOUR MAJESTY,

406
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:41,791
THAT'S KIND OF THE POINT.

407
00:21:41,875 --> 00:21:46,250
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BEAR THIS ALL
BY YOURSELF. YOU'VE GOT US NOW.

408
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:49,083
- DO I?
- OF COURSE.

409
00:21:52,041 --> 00:21:53,708
- IF ONLY...

410
00:21:53,791 --> 00:21:55,791
IF ONLY THAT WERE TRUE.

411
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:59,833
I CAN THINK OF NOTHING
I WOULD WANT MORE.

412
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:05,416
BUT THE WORLD
HASN'T CHANGED. AT ALL.

413
00:22:08,375 --> 00:22:09,875
- ( theme song playing )

414
00:22:26,958 --> 00:22:28,791
- WHAT I SEEK IS THUNDER!

415
00:22:29,541 --> 00:22:30,916
- ( yelling )

416
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,458
- IZUCHI!

417
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:38,083
- ( both yelling )

418
00:23:38,791 --> 00:23:40,708
- Ryner: SON OF A BITCH!

419
00:23:40,791 --> 00:23:42,208
WHY DO THINGS ALWAYS
GO TO SHIT

420
00:23:42,291 --> 00:23:44,000
JUST WHEN THEY'RE STARTING
TO GET BETTER?

421
00:23:44,083 --> 00:23:45,833
YOU KNOW WHAT, SION?
I DON'T CARE!

422
00:23:45,916 --> 00:23:47,458
COME AT ME WITH ALL YOU'VE GOT!

423
00:23:47,541 --> 00:23:49,750
I TOLD YOU I WOULDN'T
GIVE UP, AND I WON'T!

424
00:23:49,833 --> 00:23:53,000
NO MATTER HOW MUCH THIS TOTALLY,
COMPLETELY, TRAGICALLY SUCKS!

